head/hair style/the top/end/beginning or end/a stub/remnant/chief/boss/side/aspect/first/leading/classifier for pigs or livestock/CL:個|个[ge4]

sentences.english: Moreover, the skull has features resembling those of contemporary Asians.
sentences.chinese: 此外，该头骨具备类似现代亚洲人头骨的特征。

sentences.english: On the third flight lay a heap of dead men's heads.
sentences.chinese: 三楼上有一堆死人头呢。

sentences.english: Zhou said they have a requirement is to use twenty million in floating head.
sentences.chinese: 周院长说自己有一个要求就是用两千万换帅飘的人头。

sentences.english: Shoing malls and restaurants are once again teeming with people.
sentences.chinese: 商场和酒楼再次人头涌涌。

sentences.english: A: You need to work hard to get ahead in this company.
sentences.chinese: 在这家公司要想出人头地，就得努力工作。

sentences.english: Mistreatment by the colonial rulers and collection of a new poll tax increased tensions.
sentences.chinese: 殖民统治的虐待和新的人头税增加了紧张的气氛。

sentences.english: This paper presents a full wave analysis of electromagnetic (EM)field distribution inside a dielectric prolate spheroidal human head model.
sentences.chinese: 文中给出一长椭球介质人头模型中的电磁场全波解。

sentences.english: From the ground, it resembles a person's head surrounded by a parka hood.
sentences.chinese: 从地面上看，它就像一个戴着皮帽子的人头。

sentences.english: His head, anyway. All blood and his eyes half gouged.
sentences.chinese: 那颗人头血淋淋的，眼睛被抠出来了。

sentences.english: They know that their offspring will need English to get ahead.
sentences.chinese: 他们的后代为了出人头地将需要英语。

sentences.english: On the third flight lay a heap of dead men's heads, and they directed him still another flight higher.
sentences.chinese: 三楼是一堆死人头，它们也说教父住在上面一层。

sentences.english: I never want to view myself as any different or any better than anyone else.
sentences.chinese: 我从来没有想过要活得异于凡人或出人头地。

sentences.english: And still another type of pit is square shaped, for special burials of only human skulls.
sentences.chinese: 另外，还有一种是方形坑，是专门埋葬人头骨的。

sentences.english: The ceremony scene bobs , the people are talking with Chinese and French.
sentences.chinese: 仪式现场人头攒动，人们用汉语和法语交谈着。

sentences.english: Put out some overripe bananas with a few holes on a platform above head level.
sentences.chinese: 在比人头高的平台上放些扎了洞的过熟香蕉。

sentences.english: Millions of pianists in China were vying for fame.
sentences.chinese: 中国有成千上万的钢琴家为出人头第而拼挣。
